---
import { Code } from 'astro-expressive-code/components';

const preloadHintCode = `event: preload-hint
data: {"url": "/api/tasks", "tags": ["tasks"]}

event: preload-hint
data: {"url": "/api/user/profile", "tags": ["user"]}`;

const invalidationCode = `event: invalidate
data: {"tags": ["tasks", "task:123"]}`;

const fetchCode = `// When your code needs data
const request = new Request('/api/tasks');
const tasks = await CountCachula.fetch(request);

// Returns cached data instantly (if available)
// Then fetches fresh data in background
// UI updates automatically when fresh data arrives`;

const mutationCode = `// After a mutation on the server
await db.tasks.create(newTask);

// Invalidate related cache tags
hub.invalidate(['tasks', 'user:stats']);
// SSE automatically notifies all connected clients`;
---

<section class="py-20 px-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-white">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-purple-900 mb-6">
        How It Works
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-purple-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        Count Cachula uses server-driven invalidation and preloading to keep your client perfectly in syncâ€”without any client-side complexity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <!-- Step 1: Connection -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border-l-8 border-purple-500">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-purple-500 text-white rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-black">1</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-900">Browser Connects to SSE</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 ml-16">
          When your app loads, it establishes a Server-Sent Events connection. This gives the server a direct channel to push updates to the client.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2: Preloading -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border-l-8 border-orange-500">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-orange-500 text-white rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-black">2</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-900">Server Sends Preload Hints</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 ml-16">
          The server can immediately start warming up the cache by sending preload hints for important APIs:
        </p>
        <div class="ml-16">
          <Code code={preloadHintCode} lang="text" />
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-4 ml-16 italic">
          The client fetches and caches this data in the background, so it's ready instantly when needed.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3: Fetching Data -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border-l-8 border-green-500">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-green-500 text-white rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-black">3</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-900">Code Requests Data</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 ml-16">
          When your code needs data, it makes a normal request using Count Cachula's fetch:
        </p>
        <div class="ml-16">
          <Code code={fetchCode} lang="javascript" />
        </div>
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4 rounded ml-16 mt-4">
          <p class="text-green-900">
            <strong>The magic:</strong> Returns cached data instantly, then fetches fresh data in the background and automatically updates your UI when it arrives. No loading states needed!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 4: Mutations & Invalidation -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border-l-8 border-yellow-500">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-yellow-500 text-purple-900 rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-black">4</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-900">Mutations Invalidate Tags</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 ml-16">
          When you mutate data on the server, you invalidate related cache tags:
        </p>
        <div class="ml-16">
          <Code code={mutationCode} lang="javascript" />
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4 mb-4 ml-16">
          The server pushes invalidation events via SSE to all connected clients:
        </p>
        <div class="ml-16">
          <Code code={invalidationCode} lang="text" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 5: Real-time Updates -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border-l-8 border-red-500">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
          <div class="bg-red-500 text-white rounded-full w-12 h-12 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-black">5</div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-900">Client Updates Automatically</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 ml-16">
          When the client receives invalidation events, it automatically refetches any affected Observables and updates your UI.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-4 rounded ml-16">
          <p class="text-red-900 font-bold text-lg mb-2">
            ðŸŽ¯ This gives you REAL-TIME updates!
          </p>
          <p class="text-red-900">
            All users see changes instantly, even on pages they're not currently viewing. The cache stays warm and ready.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Benefits -->
    <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-600 to-purple-700 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 text-white">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4">ðŸ”„ Server-Driven Everything</h3>
        <p class="text-purple-100 leading-relaxed">
          The server controls invalidation and preloading, which means the client is <strong>never stale</strong>. Every fetch gets fresh data in the background, and SSE pushes immediate updates when things change.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 text-white">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4">ðŸ“ˆ Progressive Enhancement</h3>
        <p class="text-orange-100 leading-relaxed">
          Start simple with just <code class="bg-orange-700 px-2 py-1 rounded">CountCachula.fetch()</code> for automatic stale-while-revalidate. Add SSE for real-time updates. Add cache tags for smart invalidation. Add preloading for instant navigation. Build up complexity only when you need it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
